  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In German uniforms in order to demonstrate to our GIs what it would be like to encounter Germans in-- in combat and to acquaint them with the weapons that they were likely to find and how to use them.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were, of course, waiting for the invasion to start.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we had been trained to interrogate prisoners of war for-- in our case, for tactical information that would be of immediate value to-- to our troops in knowing who opposed them and in what strength and-- and with what weapons.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nine months.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we were marking time, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were trying-- we-- we ourselves received some training, but more so was the fact that we tried to train our troops and acquaint them with everything that the German army represented.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- just prior to my going in the army, I had received my last few letters that I had sent to my parents to the south of France, where they were deported in 1940 on roughly half an hour's notice to-- and--.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we still had been in touch with them and-- and had tried to get them out of there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a few times it looked as though we might get them out of there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the authorities really made it very difficult.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then also, the events overtook us again when Pearl Harbor happened and set us back to square one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was extremely difficult to get to be asked to come to the American consulate, which their nearest one was Marseille.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when you did so, you weren't assured of getting a visa.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
